# ğŸ›°ï¸ **Mapping of the Emergency Alert MBS Useâ€‘Case to IRISÂ² Subsystems**

## âœ… **1. 5GCN (Core Network)**

IRISÂ² uses a **fully integrated 5G Core Network**, supporting 5G NR NTN waveforms and multicast/broadcast services as per SpaceRise/SES technical descriptions. [\[etsi.org\]](https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/126500_126599/126502/17.00.00_60/ts_126502v170000p.pdf)

### **5GCN Functions Involved:**

| 5GCN Component                                   | Role in MBS Useâ€‘Case                                                           | Why Itâ€™s Needed                                                                                                                                                                                  |
| ------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |
| **MBS Application Server**                       | Generates & manages the emergency alert content                                | Required because 5G MBS uses applicationâ€‘layer MBS service architecture (per 3GPP TS 26.502) [\[patents.google.com\]](https://patents.google.com/patent/WO2022031915A1/en) |
| **BMâ€‘SC / MBâ€‘UPF (Broadcast/Multicast Gateway)** | Multicast session control, distribution area selection, duplication of traffic | Multicast is essential to efficiently scale NTN networks to many UEs (SES)                                            |
| **AMF/SMF**                                      | Session setup and mobility across satellite beams                              | 5Gâ€‘NTN requires robust handover management due to moving beams (SES)                                                  |
| **UDR/UDM**                                      | User groups, MBS policies, subscription data                                   | Supports which UEs are allowed to receive certain alerts                                                                                                                                         |
| **UPF (MBS User Plane)**                         | Efficient distribution of multicast flows to NTN RAN                           | 5G MBS optimizes routing for large-scale multicast delivery (3GPP) [\[key4biz.it\]](https://www.key4biz.it/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/iris2presentazione.pdf)      |

### **Key 5GCN Contribution**

*   Enables **efficient, scalable content distribution** for millions of receivers across Europe.
*   Supports **dynamic switching** between unicast/multicast, a key NTN challenge cited by SES .

