## ğŸš€ **2. NTN RAN (LEO/MEO Satellites + NTN Gateway)**

IRISÂ² includes a **regenerative 5G RAN in LEO and MEO**, using 5G NR NTN waveform in Ku/Ka bands, with full 5GC integration. [\[etsi.org\]](
https://www.etsi.org/deliver/etsi_ts/126500_126599/126502/17.00.00_60/ts_126502v170000p.pdf)

### **RAN Functions Involved:**

| NTN RAN Component                             | Role                                                                                                                                                                               |
| --------------------------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Regenerative gNodeB on LEO/MEO satellites** | Efficient satelliteâ€‘based RAN handling MBS radio bearers                                                                                                                           |
| **Multicast/Broadcast Beam Management**       | Manages dynamic MBS coverage zones over large moving footprints                                                                                                                    |
| **NTN Gateway**                               | Handles N2/N3 signaling and transport between gNB and 5GCN                                                                                                                         |
| **Beam Handover Management**                  | Critical due to moving beams and feeder link variabilityâ€”highlighted as a challenge for NTN MBS by SES  |

### **Why RAN Is Crucial**

*   Broadcast is ideal for satellite networks due to **large-area coverage** and efficient delivery of identical content to many UEs .
*   5G MBS requires NTNâ€‘specific mechanisms for **satellite-to-satellite handover**, beam switching, and delay compensationâ€”documented in SESâ€™s 5Gâ€‘NTN analysis .

